  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] All I know is that I met his wife after the war, and his two children, and he never returned.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The journey to Birkenau were really not as bad as the journey that we made to Lublin.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For some reason, they didn't have us loaded us up in the cattle train as packed as before.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they did give us some water and some food ration for the road.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the trip wasn't too long, because from Lublin to-- to Auschwitz it maybe have taken two, three hours, or maybe four hours or so forth.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they-- I remember going to through several cities, there-- to Katowice, I remember. that was the first time in my life I saw a streetcar, which I never saw at home.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And when we arrived, of course, to Birkenau, the arrival was, I mean, atrocious.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, that-- once the-- the-- the cattle train was opened up, you really saw you came into a living hell.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was the first time when we-- when we saw Mengele, when-- when dogs were barking there like you thought they're going to tear you apart.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- and I have a hard time to find even in English-- in the English language words that will be-- you were tormented for the fear of what's going to happen to you.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You felt like, any second, they're going to-- they're going to shoot you, they're going to kill you, they're going to tear you apart.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the yelling and the screaming that they created, including with the dogs, were-- were-- were awful.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, it's very hard to describe how, within seconds, you-- you realize, I've lost my identity, I'm a nobody, I'm a nothing, I'm a zero, I'm zilch.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
